# /usr/share/ollama/models/.keep
#
# Placeholder marking the build-baked, immutable model seed dir.
# automation/37-ollama-prep.sh writes manifest-style ollama model
# blobs into this tree at build time when MIOS_OLLAMA_BAKE_MODELS is
# non-empty (default: qwen2.5-coder:7b,nomic-embed-text per the
# `[ai].bake_models` field in /usr/share/mios/mios.toml). On first
# boot mios-ollama-firstboot.service hardlink-copies this dir into
# /var/lib/ollama/models/ (the writable runtime store ollama
# actually reads/writes via OLLAMA_MODELS).
#
# On MiOS-DEV (the WSL2 dev VM seeded via build-mios.ps1) the bake
# step is skipped because there is no OCI build phase; this file is
# what guarantees the directory still exists so the read-only volume
# mount in ollama.container resolves. Network fallback path in
# usr/libexec/mios/ollama-firstboot.sh handles the empty-seed case.
